content_vision: Other guys failed and even died. I'm the one out of four, which survived.
text:
Intro:
Survival of the fittest, only one made it through
I'm the one they couldn't break, they couldn't beat me, it's true.

Verse 1:
I watched my brothers fall, one by one they lost the fight,
but I held on to every shred of hope, with all my might.
They thought I'd be just another statistic,
but I proved them wrong with every note and lyric.
But my music was my lifeline, in a world that was so cruel,
it kept me going, when everything else just seemed to fail.
They laughed when I said I'll make it big, told me to stick to my day job
But now they see me on their screens, they all wanna be my squad

Pre-Chorus 1:
Feeling unstoppable, I rose from the ashes,
fueled by determination and passion.

Chorus 1:
I am the victor, the last man standing,
now they all look up to me, the one they underestimated.
I wear my scars proudly, a symbol of my strength,
I'll never falter, I'll go to any length.

Verse 2:
My brothers' dreams were crushed, their voices silenced in vain,
but I refused to let their sacrifices be in vain.
But their voices still echo in my mind,
urging me to rise and leave them all behind.
They tried to bury me in doubt, but I rose above the ground,
now I'm standing tall, while they're nowhere to be found.
I carry their dreams on my shoulders, every word
I sing is for the ones who couldn't be here longer.

Pre-Chorus 2:
I carry their legacy, it drives me and defines me,
through every challenge, I'll never be defeated.

Chorus 2:
I wear their names on my chest, a tribute to their strength,
with every beat of my heart, I'll rise above the pain.
I'll keep climbing, never looking back,
it's the path that my brothers paved.

Bridge:
I carry the weight of their dreams, on my shoulders, I'll never let them fall.
They may be gone but their spirits live on, in every note and every call.
My brothers may be gone, but I'll carry on,
their legacy lives through my song.

Outro:
My brothers may be gone, but their legacy will never fade,
their strength lives on through the music we've made.

Theme melody:
I'll carry their memories with me, through every verse and chorus,
their legacy lives on through the beats that I pour us.

Instrumental:
As the instrumental engulfs me, I feel my brothers' presence,
they're still here with me.
